Class CanonicalHuffmanRabaCoder.RabaCodingSetup

  • java.lang.Object

  • Enclosing class:
    CanonicalHuffmanRabaCoder

    protected static class CanonicalHuffmanRabaCoder.RabaCodingSetup
extends CanonicalHuffmanRabaCoder.AbstractCodingSetup
    Sets up for coding an IRaba representing B+Tree values. For this case the code book is generated from only the non-zero frequency counts. This results in a more compact code.
    Author:
    Bryan Thompson FIXME If most byte values are used, then simply code them all. This will be more efficient (smaller data record, no indirection through the symbol table).
